Package: VEL.BMGM
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Varying-Effects Logistic Regression with Mixed Graphical Structure
Version: 0.2.0
Author: Mauro Florez
Maintainer: Mauro Florez <mauroederfr@gmail.com>
Description: Implements Bayesian varying-effects logistic regression for binary
    outcomes with mixed-type predictors (continuous, discrete, zero-inflated, and
    categorical). Predictor effects are modeled as functions of external covariates
    using Gaussian Process priors. The package jointly estimates a sparse conditional
    independence graph among predictors via a Bayesian mixed graphical model (BMGM),
    leveraging spike-and-slab priors for variable and covariate selection. Posterior
    inference uses efficient MCMC with Polya-Gamma augmentation.
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports:
    BMGM (>= 0.1.1),
    mvnfast,
    MASS,
    mnormt,
    BayesLogit,
    gtools,
    scales,
    mvtnorm
Suggests:
    ggplot2,
    igraph,
    pROC
